      <title>Designation: C4-R-14</title>
      <author> Timegal25 </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1360010/designation-cr/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1360010-designation-cr/chapter/1360012/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">958d09dc6dab4a3c734407bcb742a71d28a635f7</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 25 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;A support based mech pilot has a chance encounter, starts to consider things about her place in life.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1360010-designation-cr/chapter/1360012/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Designation: C4-R-14&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“All thrusters confirmed functional in all regions. Backup fuel reserves in prime condition and full.”  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The voice echoing around in the cockpit was female. It was calm and pristine, never becoming cold. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Good. Weapon Energy?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Defensive missiles stocked. Gattling cannons stocked. Plasma cells and heating cells at full charge.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“And joints?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“All arm and leg joints have been polished and are in fully operational condition. Part check and replacement took place two nights ago. This machine was included due to your selection of ‘Automatically include in all repair and refuel sessions’ in maintenance. The total cost was 264.74 and paid automatically.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Mmm… didn’t think it would be that much,” she said with a sigh, drumming her fingers against the dashboard. “Gotta remember to get that changed. Pay’s tight as is, don’t need to lose it in huge chunks like that.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“An easy solution to that is to avoid getting into situations that would cause such damage in the first place. A reminder that you’re stationed and designated as a repair and assistance unit. Those weapons auxiliary weapons are just that: auxiliary.” Another voice came in over the comms, another female. This one was older and more mature-sounding, with a hint of being more annoyed compared to the calmer voice going over statuses. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah yeah, I know I know. Check-in complete, ready for deployment.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“The assigned task for today requires wreckage removal. A major data antenna has been reported offline. There is a high chance this is a result of a heavy snowfall and ice on the radar dish.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Should be simple enough for you. Get it, clear out whatever’s caused it to go offline, make sure it starts back up, and then come right back.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I know. Set and ready for deployment, just give the approval.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’m serious. Don’t waste your time dealing with any pointless side activities or the like. Get it done, come back, and we can discuss your future opportunities then. Do you understand?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She rubbed the back of her neck, muttering a few things before quickly nodding. “Understood ma’am.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She heard a soft chuckle come from the other end. “Very good. Then Unit C4-R-14: You are approved for deployment.”  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 smiled as she could hear the sound of the deployment alarms going off. She could see the lights of the hangar flashing red lights as her machine was bathed in their glow. It was always the take-off that got her really excited. It gave everything a whole new level of excitement. Even the most mundane, unimportant of tasks could feel like important deployments thanks to this.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She watched the hanger shutters pulled themselves open, the pale blue light from the outside world pushing against the red of the hangar. “Heading out!” she said, as she pulled on levers on her console and activated the thrusters, sending her speeding outside. While she loved the deployment sequence, her actual favorite part of being deployed was just coming up. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The world outside the hangar was pale and cold. Thick sheets of snow covered every surface that one could see. Trees, rocks, the hangar exterior. C4-R-14 wasn’t fully aware of the weather schedule, but if she had to guess, a blizzard must have passed through and given everything a fresh new coat of white… though with how the state of everything was most of the time, it wouldn’t be easy to tell which snow was fresh. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Humanity had gotten itself into another big war, this one lasting decades and decades. Was it with themselves? Other life forms? Machine? Hell if she knew, she was brought into this stuff &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;long &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;after it had started. What she did know was that as the war continued, the technology needed to progress to keep things from getting too stale or defeat becoming inevitable. Things got bigger and more electronic, and weapons more portable as they got more powerful. The end result was mechs straight off the screens of classic animated sci-fi. They had done the job just as well as all the other tech that had come before had… but then came the problem of pilots. Human pilots did the job well enough, but piloting a giant mechanical machine worked differently than what one would expect from working say a fighter jet. If a pilot died in one of these, you couldn’t just pop in a new pilot right away. They’d need a solution. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;That was where she and others just like her came in. She wasn’t a human. She was an android that looked human, sounded human, and even had a way of emulating feelings like a human…. But she wasn’t human. She was a machine— Designation: C4-R-14.  One of hundreds of other machines made to be the perfect pilots. Fatal damage taken? Just get to a repair station, and in a few hours' time,  you’ll be ready to go back out there and get back to work. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 smiled as she looked at the view she was flying over. This was her favorite part. The hanger and base she had been put up at was stationed near a bay, with any deployed units having to go over the waters when they were deployed. The way that the water would part and push away as the mech zoomed over it, the ripples that would be made as a mech hovered above it, watching it jump up into the air when thrusters increased their speed. It was a captivating sight. It made even a boring nothing deployment like this one slightly more worth it. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She had always admired watching the waters.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Task location received. Arrival will be in five minutes.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; The calm female voice said as the mech raised itself higher above the waters and into the air. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Weather has calmed down, meaning there will be no issues in moving to the location or completing the task.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Cool, cool. Begin heating the claws. Might be a help, especially on the chance we’re dealing with build-ups of ice or the like.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Understood. Claws should be fully heated in four minutes and 23 seconds.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The voice responded. Every pilot unit was also given an AI core to power the mechs. On-hand support from the hangar was always a necessity, but onboard AIs could immediately report internal damages and work to repair them or help with multi-tasking on more complicated tasks. They were never given names, simply sharing the same designations as the pilot. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 watched the scenery change as she sped off toward the target... It went from snow-covered trees and frozen waters to icy roads and dozens of communication buildings. One of the worst parts of being designated for only repair and recovery tasks was that the scenery wouldn't change. While she loved the area directly around the hanger, it was when she moved into the city that the monotony set in. The same buildings and antennas and roads, again and again. Sometimes there'd be snow, sometimes there'd be rain, sometimes it'd be completely dry. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She soared past other snow-covered antennas as her HUD led her to the one she was supposed to care about. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Claws have been fully heated and ready for work. With no interruption, this task should take approximately ten minutes.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It could be shaved down by a few minutes if usage of the plasma cutters were allowed for this one.”  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Unfortunately, usage of the plasma cutters is only recommended for emergency scenarios, as well as the high chance of the beams piercing through the ice and further damaging the antenna.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 rolled her eyes as she saw her destination up ahead. The large antenna dish was covered in large amounts of thick snow as well as thick chunks of ice in both the front dish and back supports. “Alright. Let’s get this over with,” she said as the mech’s thrusters slowed their speed and it moved to on-foot traversal. Support mechs like hers were much more shorter and compact compared to the taller and offensive-built units. They were meant to get in, do their helping task, and get out. Her mech had been given lobster-like claws instead of actual hands to help in the crushing of obstructing and harmful materials. As far as she knew, she was the unit that had these claws on her mech, so that was cool at least, right… ? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her mech’s claws reached out and clamped onto a large block of ice in the back supports. Steam quickly began to pour out as the heated claws slowly cut their way through the block. The sounds of hot metal cutting through ice were satisfying. “It’s the little things that make it worth it. Yeah, I’m not taking down enemy combatants with cool weapons or punching my way through an airship… but hey, I get to at least see some pretty things.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Your approval to join a combat unit still has not gone through, based on both your performance as well as the still pending request to deal with your internal classifications in the system.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I know that. You can stop with the automatic reminders about that kinda stuff. Already got it playing in my memory space 24/7 already…” C4-R-14 said, letting out another long sigh. When she had been originally assembled, there had been a few… defects set in place. Mech pilots were machines, but they would still be assigned gender-based identifiers. All her base info read out as being a ‘Male’ unit. Hell, when she had first been active she even believed it herself and let her body take a more masculine shape in the initial period. But she wasn’t. She was a female unit. The recognition of that fact had just come to her one day, and her systems easily accepted it as fact. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Getting her specs changed to go along with this hadn’t been easy. It would cost a lot to go through the ‘re-identification’ process since it meant having to overwrite and replace the data on her that was already in the systems and assorted combat logs. She also wanted to have her body modified to reflect her identity as well, and with how pricey getting normal repairs alone could be…  Thankfully she had been able to at least get her voice modified to have better chances of being identified as female to those she conversated with, and those she regularly worked with did refer to her with she and her tags and pronouns. Small steps that also felt big. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Honestly, I don’t even see what the issue would be with me being moved up in this state. Just have my logs and data from the moment I apply read me as female and then all I have to do is worry about fixing up the past stuff, which I’m already working towards,” C4-R-14 said, her mech cutting through the block of ice and moving its claws to another one. “I mean, mistakes happen all the time in production, so I don’t see what’s wrong with tweaking my current info to reflect myself.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“As I’ve told you a dozen times,” the female voice from the hanger chimed in over her comms. “It’s not like it’s easy to do this stuff in data and digital forms. The systems your units run on don’t work well with contradictions, and it’s not like we can just go in and simply change all your data that reads ‘he’ to ‘her’ and that would solve everything. We move you up to the combat units with the current info reading ‘her’, they do a background check and see all your data is talking about a male unit, and they see your current body, they get confused and will probably just forbid you from joining anyways. Wasting everyone’s time.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I don’t see what’s wrong with at least—”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Listen, C4-R-14. I get it. I want to see you get correct identification too. But right now there’s so much that’d need to be done that we can’t just be reckless with it. For now, we focus on getting you a good work record and making sure you’re properly prepped and ready for when you want to show off your performance skills first. We got you the voice the voice change and everyone uses ‘she/her’ for you here, so there’s no need to rush into harm.”  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 thought about things for a few seconds before slowly nodding. “Yeah… yeah, you’re right. Just gotta focus on the current jobs and work from there. Gonna finish up with the large ice blocks here first before moving to clearing out the snow on the dish.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Very good. Keep up the good work and— What the…?” The voice on the other end trailed off as C4-R-14’s HUD started to blink.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It appears there is another unit quickly approaching the area.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Is it another deployed unit returning to the hangar?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“No, no that can’t be one of ours. We only sent you out for the repair work. And as far as I know, we haven’t received any news or requests from other hangars to let one of their units rest here. Not like this is a combat interest zone either so…” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 slowly backed away from the ice she had been cutting through and turned in the direction of the approaching unit. She couldn’t see anything just yet, but she could hear something in the air. The sound of another unit’s thrusters and boosters in usage… along with what appeared to be music. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“You don’t wanna go to war with a soldier!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“You don’t wanna go to war with a soldier!”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You’re hearing that too, right?” C4-R-14 asked.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Correct. The approaching unit is playing music from their speakers.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Be ready for anything, C4. Retreat and return to base at any sign of danger.” She could see the unit in the distance, getting closer. It was a larger boxier unit, with its color scheme being a mix of black and red, with golden accents. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“There’s more to life than just fucking working, bro.” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 didn’t know what to expect, but at the least… this could be interesting.  She watched as mech touched down on the ground. It was a few heads taller than her, cradling what appeared to be a large laser rifle. It turned its head a few times, scanning the area. “Um… hi there. Are you in need of assistance or support? If so, I’m going to need to ask you to state your designation number, affiliation, and hanger base number and—” She didn’t finish her sentence as she watched the mech aim its rifle at the antenna she was working on and fire off a few shots at it, causing it to burst into a large cloud of smoke, snow, and its pieces. It then fired off a few more shots at other antennas in the area, before turning its gaze back to her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“I don’t wanna be found, I don’t wanna be downed. I don’t wanna be found, I don’t wanna be downed.” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“This mech is now classified as an enemy unit. We must retreat back to the hangar and call in combat units to deal with this threat.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“C4, get out of there now! You’re not equipped to deal with whoever that is! We’re reading combat units and sending them to your location now, just find a way to get as far away from them as you can!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“I don’t wanna be found, I don’t wanna be downed. I don’t wanna be found, I don’t wanna be downed.”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt; &lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She knew that retreat was the best option here. Her combat options were for self-defense and not offensive confrontation. Trying to take a unit like this on would cause huge damages and take an even bigger chunk out of her pay than the last one. There was just as much chance this thing would blast her to pieces as easily as it did the antennas. And yet…. And yet… and yet!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Oh you know Tyler, and his tone. I’m so sick of these niggas, they don’t know you, fuck you!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Launching missile barrage!” She said, hatches on the back of her mech opening up and a flurry of missiles raining down on the enemy unit. She quickly used her thrusters to strafe back, getting some distance from the enemy. “How close would I need to be to them to use my claws on them? Are they still heated?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Claws are still heated. Your claws’ extendable reach would allow you to physically grab onto and interact with the enemy unit from the distance of an antenna's width, however, you would likely not be able to cut directly through any part of them you clamped onto as you would the ice blocks. It is advised that you not directly confront the enemy unit. They are distracted and disoriented from the missile barrage, you have a high chance of losing them if we retreat now and use an alternate pathway to return to the hangar.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Would I be safer if I tried clamping onto a part of them from behind? They seem to have arm joints!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You would have a better chance from behind the enemy unit, yes. Their design seems to indicate their body is not built for rear offense compared to their front. However, you are being advised to return to the hangar.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“C4-R-14, just get back now. Wasting your time trying to take them on is only going to end badly for you. The missile defense gave you an opening, use it! Taking them on isn’t going to help you get moved to the combat unit any faster!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She knew she needed to listen to all these recommendations to retreat, and yet here she was using her thrusters to quickly circle the enemy mech. They were now aiming at where she was sliding, shooting up large chunks of the ground. “Firing the second barrage!” she cried, watching as another reign of missiles came down on the enemy. This time, they seemed to shrug it off as it started to speed towards her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“I got a big ol’ head I ain’t like these niggas, uh uh, don’t put me with these niggas, I don’t haha kiki with these niggas, Loiter Squad baby, I don’t be with these niggas!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She thrust up into the air, watching as the enemy sped directly under her. She landed on the ground with a thud, stabilizing herself as she boosted towards their back. She readied her claws, “directly target the arm joints, we’re aiming to clamp down on those! Begin plasma cannon charge up!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Beginning plasma charge. Cannons will be readied in approximately 15 seconds.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“And how long will it take for the targeting system to lock onto the shoulder joints?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Approximately 8 seconds.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’ll take the risk!” she said, a smile slowly coming to her face. She was directly in danger, taking this on by herself and not even waiting for backup. And yet, she was having the time of her life. It was like every part of her operating system was being used to its full potential. She had no idea as to what the extent of the kinds of sensations and emotions could be emulated… but she was pretty sure she was experiencing euphoria right now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Don’t be stupid, C4! You’ve got another chance to get out of there! Move now! Actual combat units are on this way and will actually be able to handle this more than whatever you’re trying here!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She zoomed in closer, readying the claws as target reticles appeared in her HUD. They slowly started to circle in on the enemy’s shoulder joints. Then, the enemy unit raised one of their arms, now hoisting the barrel of the rifle over their shoulder, and letting off a few shots.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 felt her entire mech violently shake and rattle with each shot that hit, bouncing her around in her cockpit. “Ngh! Damage report!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Damage to the main chest piece of this unit. No damage to any vital components or AI core, but it has slowed our approach. Large chance of that being a warning shot.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“And what about our targeting, how are we on that?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Targets locked. Our pursuit has slowed. To get into grabbing range would leave us open to more direct hits.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“We’re in too far, we’re gonna have to just take it!” she said, re-engaging the thrusters. She watched as the enemy fired off a few more shots, seeing as large chunks of her own mech were sent flying off from the hits. “Sorry, but I’m not backing down that easy! My turn, jackass!” she said, smiling still as the claws shot out and clamped down onto the enemy mech’s shoulder joints, steam already starting to pour out from the heat searing down onto them. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“They are starting their thrusters back up. By increasing their distance, they have a good chance of ripping our claws off and leaving us defenseless.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Guess we just won’t let that happen! Activate plasma cutter, full burst shot!” C4-R-14 said, slamming her fist down on the control console. She was smiling from ear to ear as she heard the sounds of the cutters activating. After a few seconds, she watched as bright blue beams of plasma shot through the enemy mech’s shoulders, followed by the claws cutting through them and sending both arms and the rifle falling to the ground and kicking up huge snow clouds beneath them. “Yes! Yes Yes Yes!” she cheered, pumping her fist in celebration. “Retract claws. Now we can focus on getting a retreat route that doesn’t lead them directly back to base and—”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The head of the enemy mech suddenly twisted around, looking directly at her. “Is this all that you aspire for?” they asked, a woman’s voice coming out of their speakers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“... Huh?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Do you aim for more purpose? Or do you think the only way of being is following the commands of others. As a support, as a combatant. Do you think your only true purpose is to be a unit to others who only see you for your data?” Suddenly, steam came up from the top of the enemy mech’s head. Slowly, she watched as the mech’s pilot crawled out. They were dressed in a crimson red pilot suit, with long flowing black hair and piercing yellow eyes. They slowly reached at their chest, digging their fingers into their outfit before yanking on it tearing off some of it and revealing her chest. Her skin was midnight black, C4-R-14 unable to look away from it. Then she noticed, the pilot’s breasts, there were lines along their edges. They had been part of the pilot’s body and had been attached or modified. This unit was like her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...What? Who are you? What are you talking about?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You are more than any of this. So much more! Allow yourself to fully become who you know you are! Your true purpose grasped and explored!” the pilot shouted, continuing to look directly at the mech’s cockpit… no directly at C4-R-14. They then smiled, bowed, and hopped back into their mech. And before C4-R-14 could fully respond, the enemy mech quickly sped off to the distance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 just stood there, watching the mech speed off, getting smaller and smaller before becoming a tiny spec on the horizon and vanishing into the grey clouds and snowy environment. She laid back in her cockpit, listening to the sounds of its multiple components at play as well as the sounds of nature outside. She softly massaged the sides of her cheeks with her fingers. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“C4-R-14?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Hm? Yeah, what is it?” she asked her AI. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You have disabled your comms with the hangar and haven’t made any orders to return. Are your systems damaged? It is unlike you to go silent for so long.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh. No, no. Just trying to piece together whatever just happened. Probably should start to get back to base, yeah? Let other units clean this mess up and get ready for whatever the repair costs are,” she said, leaning back towards her controls before pausing. “Actually… can we just stay here a few minutes longer before returning to base? It’s honestly been a while since I’ve been outside, and I just wanna appreciate the change of space a bit longer.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“... There is no harm in that. No reports of other enemy/unknown units approaching.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She always liked the times when her AI core showed signs and bits and pieces of a personality. With AI cores being so connected to their pilots, it was bound to happen, even if it felt like they tried to keep the AI as blank and detached by not giving them physical forms or names of their own. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The two sat there, simply watching the snow fall over the newly destroyed area. The antennas damaged would probably cause some havoc among the hangars and their assorted units for a while, but it would likely just be a temporary setback and nothing else. They listened to the sound of the wind blowing. “The damage that mech did to this thing. How bad was it?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Aside from the loss of several components of the exterior chest piece, there was nothing vital or critical was damaged. The type of energy used seemed to be different than the ones used in attacking the antenna. Their message to you makes me assume that the enemy pilot never had any intention of doing fatal harm to us if any actual harm at all.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 thought on the pilot’s words again before nodding. “Is my kind of… situation common among pilots?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I cannot say. I do not have access to that kind of production data if changes in a pilot’s gender and presentation are even recorded in the first place.”  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thought as much.” She let out a long sigh. “Alright, I think that’s been enough time. Returning to the hangar and reporting in on the results of this task.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Affirmative. Letting the hangar know we are on our way back. I assume you wish to keep the comms off.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, I think I’ll go with getting yelled at only when we get back. Instead, select one of the tracks from my playlist. Help make the scenery look even more beautiful.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I’ll see what I can do.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 smiled as her thrusters started back up and she began flying back to base. There was a feeling of relief within her as she saw the trees and the water return. It was like she was a bird, taking off and flying over the sea. The sounds of an orchestra playing through the cockpit just made the image of flying over the water even more welcoming. If she didn’t have to be back to base, she would’ve just done that for a few hours to come off of what had happened. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;As the hangar’s shutters opened and she slowly placed herself down on a launch pad, she disconnected herself from the cockpit. “Hey. That song that pilot was playing. You know what it was?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“‘Thought I was Dead’ by Tyler the Creator, off his album ‘Chromakopia’. Would you like me to add the album to your listening playlist for later?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah. Always nice to add more stuff to that one. I’ll see you back in my room, after I’m done getting scolded. Great work as always, C4-R-14.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You as well, C4-R-14. I will meet you there.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The AI said as the lights in the cockpit slowly turned off, one by one. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 smiled as she made her way to the exit hatch. Already, she could hear a few voices outside calling for her. They did not sound happy. “Alright. Time to face the music, I guess,” she said, opening the hatch and hearing it hiss.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;— &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I want you to actually listen to what I’m saying. I’m not trying to yell at you because I want you to feel bad about everything that happened. I want you to think about everything that happened and see what you can learn from it. Yes, you did a good job, but you were in so much danger that the risk more outweighed it than anything else.” The talking down that C4-R-14 wasn’t as scream-heavy as she expected it to be, but it was a lot of dressed-up talking down. She was still being talked down to by one of the hangar’s commanders and Superiors: simply known to her as a Superior. An older woman who had just as much chance of being a human as she was a machine. Maybe everyone in this hangar was a machine and she just wasn’t let in on it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 just kept walking down the hallway back to her room, her shoes clanking against the metallic floor in a rhythm. “I know, I’ve heard you. Just let me get back to my room and… decompress from all of that. I can log a full report and plan up better strategies for next time, I promise,” she said, massaging the sides of her cheeks as she kept walking. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I get it. You did a fantastic job out there for a support droid. I would never deny that, promise. If there’s a way for me to help get you looked at for being moved to the combat unit in the future, I will. But—” The Superior paused, thinking on her words. “&lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;And&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;, you were reckless and in a lot of spots that put you in danger. You’re lucky the damage your mech received was minimal and nothing fatal. If one of those explosive shots had nailed your chest or even a bit closer up, you’d be in the repair bay right now and out of commission for who knows how long.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I know. I know. I know.” C4-R-14 knew to tread carefully. This woman was designated her Superior. She was given that kind of position due to the kind of knowledge she had. But really, she didn’t need to hear this. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The Superior looked down a the floor and let out a long sigh. She then pulled C4-R-14 into a hug. “I know that you really want to get some of those adjustments on yourself done. You want to be in combat and you want everyone to refer to you as a female unit. I get why you’d think doing this would help with that. But it’s just not that easy. How I wish it was.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 looked aside as she heard this. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s gonna take a bit more for these things to happen, but you know you have me and everyone else here. We all use your right pronouns on you, and we all see you as a woman just as you do. You have things going for you here, don’t rush something like this. You have no idea what could be waiting for you on the other side. Just keep sticking to the welcoming you get here and we can work on taking steps to the bigger stuff soon enough. I promise.” The Superior stepped away, keeping her hands on C4-R-14’s shoulders and smiling down at her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 nodded, weakly smiling back. “Alright. I’ll keep doing my best at being a support unit and hope for the best.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The Superior patted her on the head before letting go of her shoulders. “Very good. I’ll leave you to work on your data report of events. The enemy’s attacks on the area’s antennas knocked us out of the area’s cameras and the getting and sending reports to other hangars and units. We’re a bit in the dark right now, but I think all of us here can still make it work and get all of that stuff fixed,” she said, before turning and starting to leave. “Report on any details you could get on that enemy mech, finding out more about them or even an estimate on where they were headed could get data on any groups they were possibly attached to.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Her.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Huh?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Before the enemy mech retreated, she talked to me. The pilot unit was a female.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh, that’s good. Include that in the report. I look forward to reading it!” the Superior said before continuing their way down the hall and out of C4-R-14’s sight. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 watched the hallway she had gone down for a few seconds, standing there alone in complete silence. She then turned back around and continued to her room.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her room wasn’t anything special. Just a desk with a computer attached, a standing charging station/bed, and a few large screens that covered the walls adjacent to the charging pod. There were a few posters she had set up on the other walls of the room, photos of other female pilots, and their massive mechs. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;These rooms used to belong to the old pilots, back when they were humans. This meant that every room had an attached bathroom and shower. Now, this was used mostly as storage space or the like since no matter how advanced tech got, showers weren’t meant for robots. If a pilot got their skin dirty or torn, the repair bay was the place to go to get that addressed. Most pilots didn’t even use the room at all, having the door locked. C4-R-14 kept hers because of the mirror. She liked to look at herself from time to time. After missions, random times of the night, when she first activated for the day. It was a nice thing to do. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She approached her bathroom mirror and gazed at her reflection. She smiled at the cutie looking back at her, running a hand through her curly hair. She then realized she still had her gloves on, before pulling them off and giggling. “It’s weird. Having all these feelings and emotions adds very little to these parts of my operating, and yet… I am happy I have them. That I look human,” she said, admiring her dark brown skin. “Maybe it’s just it allows me to admire the colors around me more. Maybe I wouldn’t like watching the water as much if my eyes weren’t the same color,” she pondered as she leaned in closer, looking at her reflection’s green eyes—the same green as the ocean, the same green as her pilot suit. She ran her ungloved hands over the markings under her eyes, feeling the cold steel plating.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She made faces at her reflection for a bit, giggling all the while. “Can’t believe I’m someone they think should be in a giant robot helping with things,” she said, smiling. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You do a good job at it, C4-R-14,”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; the voice of the AI responded, her voice coming from speakers placed throughout both rooms. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“While your repair prices can be a bit higher than most other support units, your data reports give better results than what is expected for a non-combat-focused unit.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thanks. Being a support unit isn’t bad or anything,” C4-R-14 said, heading back into her main room. “But I’m allowed to want more. I’ve been in the position for at least a few years. Something’s gotta chance sooner or later.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Other units from this hangar have been moved up. It is likely that you have a high chance of being one of them if you are able to keep damage report numbers down.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I guess. I guess,” she took a seat at the desk, reaching for a cable from the computer and connecting it to the back of her neck. She began filing a report on the mission, trying to include as many details as she could.  When it came to talking about her confrontation with the other pilot, she paused. It would be easy to include details of her physical appearance, she had made it obvious she wanted C4-R-14 to look at her closely… but those words she had said. They were sticking with her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I believe the reason for the song choice used when approaching and confronting you is due to the fact that your pilot suit bears a resemblance to the suit used in promotional material and the album cover for ‘Chromakopia’.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“... she didn’t use lethal or even damaging rounds on me, she got out of her cockpit even with her mech disabled, she looked directly at me and showed me her body… she wanted to personally confront me.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It seems that is the most likely possibility. However, there are no reports of any unknown units being in the area when you were doing other support work. At least nothing I’ve been able to find in the last year. But, due to the mech and pilot not being in any systems that could make her easily identifiable, it is likely we were simply unaware of her.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That message was for me. She was just like me… huh…” C4-R-14 leaned back in her seat, looking up at the ceiling. “... Finishing up report,” she said, sending the data and unplugging herself from her computer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She made her way back to the bathroom and looked at her reflection again. She smiled again, looking at herself… but there was something off. There was happiness in her, happiness with the work that she did and getting commended for it, happiness with the visions that she had of being moved up to a combat unit for her skills… but there was also something missing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She pulled off her other glove and started to move her hands down her chest, feeling her body underneath the suit. Yes, she was a female unit. She recognized herself as that. She was allowed to wear the female uniform. Everyone around the base called her a female, and they even used the right pronouns for her. This was all good. This was all in her favor. And yet… and yet… and yet… something was missing. And she knew what it was. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She felt as if there was little chance for her to continue being a woman. The state of being she was in right now, that was the furthest she would be allowed to go. They’d call her by the pronouns she wanted while she was here, they’d recognize her as a female pilot. They’d give her the female outfits. They’d let her change her voice, though she had done that by herself without much assistance from anyone else at the hangar. But getting her body changed to reflect that? Getting her past data changed to reflect who she was? Being recognized as a female pilot by other hangars and units? That was too risky to just charge into or just do on a whim. So she’d have to wait. And wait. And wait. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She’d wait for something that would likely never come if she continued to stay and work here. Her Superior, she would smile and hug her and give her words of support. But… there was a slight sense of hollowness to it. Like it was encouraging her as she was now, and not who she could be. They already called her a woman here, so that was all she needed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 was allowed to become the woman she knew she was. But she was only allowed to stay as a woman in a way that was acceptable around here. One that wouldn’t require too much work or focus or time, one that wouldn’t risk or interrupt any relationships with the outside world. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 was still a robot mech pilot. One meant to follow the directions of others and follow whatever tasks were assigned to her. And fully becoming a female unit simply didn’t play into those tasks and needs. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“... She was just like me…” she said to herself, as she slowly turned away from the mirror. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“ C4-R-14. Would you like to talk with me about what you’re feeling?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The AI asked, a hint of concern in her voice. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, that’d… that’d be good actually. Though, I don’t really like just talking to nothing. I’m gonna head back to the mech and I can talk with you in the cockpit.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“There is no need for that. Allow me a few seconds to properly join you.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt; C4-R-14 didn’t know what to expect when she heard the sounds of clanging and banging echo out around the room, followed by a crystal-like ball falling onto the desk with a &lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;thunk&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;. She looked at it in silence, softly poking at the thing before straightening up as she saw a pair of digital eyes appear in the center of the ball. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“This is my core. While I am typically stored in our mech, as it is the spot of all AIs activation, I am allowed to store myself in the core and move it around as needed. Typically for events as being connected to an external system to go through all the data that I have recorded, or when we are being moved to a new mech.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I see,” C4-R-14 said, slowly picking up the core and raising it to her eye level. While it was a bit hard to make out through the crystalline material, she was pretty sure the AI had the same eye colors of sea green as she did. “Well, it’s nice to have something to attach to your voice, after all you’ve done to help me out in the field.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You do not need to give me any thanks. Assisting you is part of my purpose and function. We are part of the same mech and share the same designation.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Would you like to be called something different? Like, would you want to be seen as a separate being from me, or do you want to just be as you are?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“An interesting query. As your AI, sharing your designation has simply been accepted as part of who I am. Helping you is what I am made to do, and while I do not fully know if I have emotions on the same level as you do, it does make me feel some sense of satisfaction that I am fulfilling my programming but also just that I am helping you. In terms of having my own designation, if that would help you… please refer to me as Carolyn.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 blinked at the name chosen, but then she gave Carolyn a big smile. “Alright. I can work with that. It’s a good name, close enough to what mine is.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Would you like to be referred to with a more personal name as well?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She thought about it, before shaking her head. “Nah… I like the designation I got. It’s me,” she said, sitting back down with Carolyn. “I think it just comes from the fact that I’m being referred to at all, which makes me happy. Or at least, it did. It doesn’t anymore. Not as much as it used to.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Is there something that can be done that would help you feel better?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Yeah, knowing that I’m not stuck against a wall would be something… My true purpose. That’d be nice to know. I didn’t know I could have a true purpose outside what I was built for.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 rocked back and forth in her chair, thinking about the other pilot. The way she had shown off her chest so proudly, she had wanted to show C4-R-14 there were more like her, that she could get a body like that. An open invitation to something greater. Helped that she was a real cutie too, especially with that smile she had given her. “I think, I’d feel better if I saw that pilot again. She said all that and then just dipped, did she want me to follow her? Was she hoping I’d say something specific to her? I wanna just find her and talk. The way she looked at me. I wanna talk, and I wanna hear her talk directly to me again. She saw me.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“The way you are talking about the other pilot, you are implying you’d wish to visit her outside of the approved vision of this hangar.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“... If I tell you that is correct, are you going to alert any of the Superiors?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“No, I would never. We are forever connected, and I am meant to aid you. If you wish to find and conversate with the unknown pilot again, I shall do what I can to help in finding her. But, I would not know where to start, and if you wish to look without any Superior knowing, it may be more difficult.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 nodded to this, thinking about things. She went back to the bathroom and looked at her reflection. She was still smiling, she was still happy with herself, who she was, and the work she had done… but it was becoming less and less connected to this place. The halls were becoming more cold and metallic, the room more empty and lifeless. There wasn’t a need for much customization or personality in these things, they were just robot pilots after all. They didn’t use the showers, eat, or even need a bed! They just plugged into their computers and submitted their data. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What if… what if we just left this place? If we got in our mech, picked and direction, and just went off. We can probably use some data from that confrontation to at least estimate where she was headed. I mean, she lost her arms, she needs to have someplace to go to get them repaired, right?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“...” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You can tell me if this is a bad idea, or that this place has our best interests in mind.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I am just trying to figure if this is a valid option. I am surprised by this turn. You have stated your want to be moved to a combat unit multiple times, and even today it is what influenced your actions. What made you change up?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Just going over some stuff and having some revelations. A place like this, it was nice at first. But then, things just stagnated and it makes me wonder if my reception and treatment were ever genuine in the first place. Soon enough, I just won’t like being here at all. And I can’t risk getting that other pilot in danger if I tried to look for her while still being connected to here.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“There are many risks that would come from making such a move. By disconnecting ourselves from this hangar and its affiliations, we would be on our own, needing to find solutions that would arise from things like damage to ourselves or our mech or running low on resources like charge.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I mean, could we load my charging pod into the mech?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“That is a possibility. Then the problem would shift into trying to find where a power source for it would be.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“So… this is a bad idea, then?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It is a dangerous one. But, I will do my best to assist you in finding the woman if you truly believe your time here is not helping you in any way. Our best time to leave without much fuss would be to take off later on in the night, when any security in the deployment bay and around the hangar, in general, is lower than during active duty hours. As well, it would be good to order a refueling of any fuel and weapon supplies before departure as well. It will leave us with a slightly tighter credit budget if we do this.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 nodded, smiling as she softly rubbed the top of the core. “Thank you, Carolyn. I don’t think I’d be as happy if I didn’t have you alongside me.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thank you, C4-R-14. I shall do all that I can. Do know that we only have one chance at doing this.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s a chance I’m more than willing to take.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;—&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Making their way back to the mech had been as easy as expected. All the pilot units were back in their rooms and the security cameras were easy to avoid. Even the ones that covered the mech hangar wouldn’t be that big of a concern until morning when they were both long gone. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14’s mech still had a few pieces from where it had been blasted in the chest, but that was nothing. It was restocked and refueled, and the damage wasn’t even that noticeable from a standstill probably.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 was silent as she got back into her cockpit and reconnected herself to her mech. She didn’t have a heart or anything that required her to need oxygen, but she was still making sounds to emulate deep, soothing breaths. “I need to see her again. I need to talk.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Opening the hangar doors will set off the deployment alarm, but by the time anyone reaches us, we should have already taken off. I cannot say if they will send anyone after us at that point, but hopefully, us doing this so late at night will send the right message or cause them to lose interest.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thanks, Carolyn. I’ll find some way to properly pay you back for all of this when we’re out of here.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“There is no need to—”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt; &lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I know there isn’t, but let me do it anyway!” C4-R-14 said, patting her console and smiling. She took another deep breath as she heard the deployment alarm start to go off, the whole hangar being covered in red. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Deployment Platform activated. Ready thrusters for take-off, the bay doors should be open in a few minutes' time.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 nodded as she moved her hands to the control, hearing the mech’s trusters hum as they began warming up.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;CLANK. CLINK. CLANK. &lt;/b&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Those weren’t sounds she had ever heard before when waiting for deployment.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“What exactly do you think you’re doing, C4-R-14?” The voice of her Superior came in over the comms and she began to shake in her seat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Warning, there are several restraining cuffs now active on this mech’s joints. Attempting to move with them on would cause major strain and tearing to the mech.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You’ve never gone for any type of late-night joy rides as long as I’ve known you, and there hasn’t been word of an emergency surprise mission. So, are you going to tell me what you’re doing here or are you going to leave your mech silently?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 silently sat in her cockpit, hands trembling. Should she just lie and go back to her room without much trouble? Take the easiest route? &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The image of the other pilot looking right at her and smiling flashed through her head. Such a pretty, happy smile. She needed to see her again. She took a deep breath. “I’m putting in the request to be dismissed from this hangar.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“... I see. I’m guessing this relates to whatever happened with that other mech that you didn’t include in your report. It just abruptly ended. Unfortunately, I’m not going to let you just take off like that. Being reckless is only going to get you hurt.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I don’t like being here anymore. I feel like I’ve done all I need to in my time as a support unit and if nothing’s going to change here, then I need to get out and find change myself.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Ah. So this is you throwing a temper tantrum about everything. How about you come out and we talk about this, yeah?” The Superior’s voice had no sense of warmth behind it, real or feigned. She wasn’t in the mood for any of this right now. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“I can talk fine with you right here, thank you. I’m not feeling welcomed by your words and I don’t want to take any chances.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She heard the Superior sigh. “C4-R-14. I’m tired. Please just come out of there and tell me why the sudden change. I don’t want to get aggressive. I don’t know what happened with that other mech pilot, but I promise you that we can come to an agreement on it.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;There was part of her that was considering this option. Maybe the Superior would be more willing to listen to her wants and needs to just get this over with. Maybe she’d be down with looking into ways to get other hangars and units to recognize her as a woman. Maybe… maybe… &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;No. That wasn’t right. She didn’t want it like that. Being acknowledged only as a form of quickly dismissing a problem and not out of actual care and recognition. She didn’t want that. She didn’t want to be surrounded by others that didn’t actually care. Hollow gestures weren’t what she needed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“C4-R-14. Are you ready to come out and talk?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Are you willing to help me continue in my transitioning process? I want my old data finally changed to reflect my proper gender and identity!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Oh my god, you’re actually doing this. C4-R-14, get out of your mech and come to me right now. Usage of your mech outside of deployment is not allowed and will result in penalties taken out of your personal balance. I’m not playing about this, C4-R-14. Get out of there now before I &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;really &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;start getting angry. Especially after everything else that happened today.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 didn’t need to breathe, she had no lungs, but she could still feel her own breath stop at this. She was shaking again. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“You are the light. It’s not on you, it’s in you. Don’t you ever, in your motherfucking life, dim your light for nobody!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Music began playing, filling the entire hangar. C4-R-14 realized it was coming from her own mech’s system this time. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Do not give up now. If this means so much to you, you should not fold.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Calm down, sit still, that’s one mil for each wheel. Top down, big deal how the fuck he do that?”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“C4-R-14, I am not in the mood to play games with you right now. I’ve told you time and time again, that these things take time. It’s a process. You’re just anxious over whatever happened. As a pilot, you’re expected to be mature and handle these things with respect. Don’t make me start thinking I was wrong about that.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“What the fuck I look like? Get the fuck up out him way.” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She could hear her mech straining as she tried to raise up its claws. The sounds of the thrusters were getting louder, building up more and more energy. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Hawthorne is where I’m from, another planet where him stay.” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“We already see you as a woman here. We already let you wear the female outfits and use the pronouns you asked for. If this is because another unit got them wrong or the like, let me know. I will deal with these things, but you need to know they will happen! This isn’t worth kicking up such a storm!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Fifteen cash for that new fort, I had guap since I was nineteen.”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 increased the thrusters’ power more, bit by bit. She was trying to down the Superior’s voice as she shook in her spot. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“I popped out like cha-ching, I think I’m a goddamned fiend!”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You think I can just go and do something for you on a whim like this? That I can go to whatever archive I can and flip a switch and that’s it? No, it isn’t! It takes time! It takes effort! It takes convincing! My position could be in danger by doing it, do you understand that? Do you really want me to risk that just because you want something here and now?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Really balling in this bitch, I’m the hardest in this bitch. Give a fuck about no bark, I’m chasing dogs up in this bitch!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She didn’t say anything in response. She just focused on the hangar doors. She had no idea on how she was going to get out of them, even if she did get free from the cuffs. Maybe the claws could wrench them open?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“El Segundo felt like coliseum, P said I could do it too and boy did I believe him!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“If I lose my position, you don’t get any protections. If the next Superior doesn’t want to humor you, then that’s it for any of the liberties you’ve got here right now!” The Superior’s voice was getting angrier and angrier. C4-R-14 could even see her pop up on the HUD. She was standing on a platform overlooking the departure bay. She looked so small and powerless and yet her words were booming and echoing. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“I built a path of freedom ‘cause them words that he said:” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“And let’s say it works and you get moved to a combat unit. Do you think they’re gonna be nice to you? Those are pilots who are out there taking down the enemy and risking getting destroyed. They’re not gonna be in the mood to listen to you have to explain everything. And with all that fighting, you think you’re gonna have the time to get any body modifications? Let me tell you, you aren’t. You’ve always had the best chance here! We gave you what you asked for, no complaining! Why can’t you just be thankful for that, why do you want even more?!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Give a fuck about tradition, stop impressing the dead!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thrusters at nearing one hundred percent. The cuff durability dropping. Hangar shutters are locked. Trying to consider any possible routes of escape. Any suggestions are welcomed.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“I’m gon make it out, promise I’m gon make it out, mama, I’m gon make it out, pussy, I’m gon make it out!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Her whole mech was shaking as she tried to make it move. Even with the roar of thrusters, she could still hear the Superior’s voice over her comms. Just getting harsher. There was no warmth, no attempt to play nice. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 leaned forward in her seat, manually increasing the thruster’s power even more. She could see the other pilot’s face flashing through her head. She was smiling again, nodding to her. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“I ain’t never had a doubt inside me, and if I ever told you that I did, I’m fucking lying!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“We are putting considerable strain on the mech, but the cuffs are wearing thin. We just need a bit more of a push and we should be able to get free of them.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Can you feel the light, inside can you feel that fire?” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“You really think you know what’s best for yourself, huh? C4-R-14, that world outside will not care about you one bit. The second you try to feed those delusions of yours more, you will be hurt and realize this was the only place that would treat you right. We are what’s keeping you safe, we are what’s keeping you happy. No one else will ever, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;ever&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;, give you the respect you think you deserve. So, I’m telling you one, last time. Get out of your mech.”&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Can you feel the light, inside can you feel that fire?”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Right. This. Instant!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Fire.”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 felt her fist slam down on the console dashboard as she leaned forward in her seat. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Fire!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thrusters to two hundred percent power!” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;In mere seconds, C4-R-14’s mech broke free of its restraints, boosting into the air with its thrusters melting the scaffolding behind it. It then soared right at the exit shutters, smashing right through them as it flew out into the night sky. C4-R-14 saw the huge chunks of metal plating slide off her HUD as if they were bugs on a windshield. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She was outside. She had left the hangar and was now floating over the bay waters again. She could hear the alarms going off behind her alongside the roar of her overcharged thrusters, but the voice of the Superior was no longer in her comms. As she watched the waters below push itself away from her thrusters, she leaned back in her chair and laughed. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“We have left. We must make a move now, before our old bosses try anything. I fear they will not hesitate in trying to dispose of us,” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Carolyn said, breaking C4-R-14 out of her stupor. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Which way do you suggest we head? I will need time to calculate a guess on where that other pilot headed.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;There was little time to think rationally. She watched the water more, before she smiled again. “Follow the water of the bay. While most missions had go to the town in front of the hangar, this time we’re following the water and going behind it!” she said, hands back on the controls as she zoomed off into the unknown. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;In the moonlight, she watched as the waters reacted to her mech. The way it made waves pushing away, the way it crashed and rippled from her presence. It was truly mesmerizing, and now she could watch it whenever or however she wanted. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“How are you feeling after pulling this off, C4-R-14?” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Good. It’s a good start. Now, let’s see where it goes…” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;— &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The sounds of ocean waves crashing against the shore had made for such a nice replacement for the cold and empty sounds of metal hallways and industrial cooling fans. Even when she thought she’d get bored of it, she’d re-activate to the sound at the start of a new day and it would just feel so right. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;She and Carolyn had been on their own for a few days now after their late-night escape. There hadn’t been any units sent to try and re-capture them or even just terminate them, so that was a relief, though it did cement to her that leaving that place was the best move if she was seen as so disposable like that. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 had done her best to try and use data on the area to try and guess where that other pilot had gone, but most of their searching had turned up little. Most days were spent flying in a specific direction and hoping to find anything but there were little results. A few new abandoned towns and some nearby mountains but no unknown mechs. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;Every day, after their search, they would return to their current base of operations: a nearby beach. It provided the most open space for the mech to be placed compared to all the cramped trees and buildings. If it was a taller combat-focused mech that’d be no issue, but this tiny crab-clawed support unit was simply going to have to stay out in the open. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“We should have enough fuel to last us a few more days of open searching, though it would mean we’d have to avoid combat if a scenario arose, as I’m currently routing all power consumption that would normally be used for the plasma cutters,” Carolyn explained, looking out at the water from her AI core. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 nodded as she continued to look out and watch the ocean waves crash against the sands. This was their routine. They’d wake up early, get out of the mech, and watch the waters while going over. They do the same upon returning at night as well. “I think maybe we if did searching for two days in a row, maybe we’d have a good chance of finding a new area as well. If we lower the power of the thrusters as well to help the battery last even longer.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It is a possibility worth considering.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The two continued to watch the waters silently. Despite everything that had happened over the past few days, and how aimless and chaotic everything was right now… C4-R-14 still felt this sense of relief that hadn’t left. “You know, even if we never do find that pilot again, I’m happy with being out in the world like this. We can just focus on trying to find a new place for us to exist and how to continue on by ourselves if we need to. As long as I’ve got you, I think I’ll be able to do well.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Thank you for your compliments, C4-R-14. I shall continue to do my best to try and find the other pilot, but if that is your new goal, I will happily assist in that as well.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;They heard footsteps approaching behind them as C4-R-14 turned and looked. The other pilot was there, wearing a new, non-torn, outfit. She approached the two, standing next to C4-R-14 and looking out to the ocean. “I’m sorry for not finding you sooner. Getting arm repairs takes a bit more time to work on compared to just getting a few scratches or the like,” she said, chuckling. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“Not a problem. Honestly, I think time away from others in general has been good for my head. Too much stuff I needed to process and take in and go over again and again. The sounds of the ocean are helpful with that,” C4-R-14 responded, watching her. She was so stunning to look at. She couldn’t move her gaze away. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Don’t you ever stop being who you are, and dimming your light for none of these motherfuckers out here!” &lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It’s nice to finally see you again. I’ve got so much I want to ask you and talk to you about. So much that I hope you’d be able to help me with,” she said, turning to face the other woman. She extended a hand. “My name is C4-R-14. This is my AI, Carolyn. I think I’m just like you and would love to know more about what that means.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;“It is a pleasure to meet you again, miss.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;“Can you feel light, inside, can you feel that fire?”&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;The other pilot smiled, taking C4-R-14’s hand and shaking it. “It’s a pleasure to meet you both as well. My designation is A1-L-13. But, I would prefer if you called me Alice. And please, you’re free to ask me anything you want. We’ve got all the time in the world now.” &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:400"&gt;C4-R-14 looked at Alice and flashed her a big grin. She hoped this was the start of something truly beautiful. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
