      <title>I Already Knew</title>
      <author> zyllycat </author>
      <link>https://www.scribblehub.com/series/1351967/i-already-knew/</link>
      <comments>https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1351967-i-already-knew/chapter/1357379/#comments</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">fe9ee8f639d7085a13200e5db747c44b7df4bb06</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 25 Dec 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div class="wi_fic_desc" property="description"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Ethan’s got a bit of a crush on his friend Sage, and today’s the day he’ll finally ask them out.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.scribblehub.com/read/1351967-i-already-knew/chapter/1357379/"&gt;&lt;div class="chapter-title"&gt;Oneshot&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;div class="chp_raw" id="chp_raw"&gt;&lt;div class="wi_authornotes"&gt; &lt;div&gt; &lt;div class="p-avatar-wrap"&gt;&lt;a class="avatar has-link" href="/profile/151855/zyllycat/"&gt;&lt;img id="acc_ava_change profile" alt="" src="https://cdn.scribblehub.com/avatar/s/37/ava_151855_1706554857.jpg"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="an_username"&gt;&lt;a href="/profile/151855/zyllycat/"&gt;zyllycat&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style="clear: both;"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="wi_authornotes_body"&gt;  hi all it’s zyllycat with my first (released and finished) foray into our beloved transfic community! hope you enjoy! &lt;img src="https://www.scribblehub.com/wp-content/themes/writeit-child/emojis/blobs/blobcat_smile.png" alt="blobcat_smilee" width="20" height="20" /&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     The sun pierced through the scattered clouds and shone in Ethan’s eyes as he walked down the street looking for the coffee shop displaying a pride flag in the front window. His friend Sage frequents there Thursday afternoons to study, and occasionally Ethan drops by before his afternoon class to hang out even though it’s in the opposite direction of campus. Upon entering he was greeted with the typical bustling activity of the place: the whirring of blenders and grinders, the indistinct chatter of people in line and at nearby tables, and the clacking of keys from the mechanical keyboard club that meets here weekly. As Ethan waited in line—he’d always feel bad coming without buying anything—he scanned the place for his friend until he found them sitting at a half booth table by themselves hunched over their laptop, dressed in their typical, lazy-day, gender-ambiguous look of an oversized sweater and standard fit men’s jeans. After placing his order, Ethan took a few deep breaths. “Okay, you can do this,” Ethan whispered to himself then got lost in his thoughts as he approached, ‘You’ve learned a lot about queer people from being around Sage this past year, and with that perhaps developing a crush on Sage might not have been the straightest thing to do. Wait, but if they’re nonbinary and you’re a cis guy, does that mean it’s still technically strai—’&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     Ethan was swiftly ejected from his thoughts as he barely grazed a nearby table within Sage’s earshot, smacking his foot on one of the chair legs, causing him to wince and Sage to look up from their computer.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Ethan!” Sage lit up and got up and gave Ethan a hug to help him stabilize. “You okay?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “H-hey Sage,” Ethan got out, “yeah just a little hitbox oversight, you know me,” trying to chuckle it off as Sage guided him back to their booth.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Soooo,” Sage began, sitting down next to Ethan with their arms now over his left shoulder, “what’s up? You don’t often get that zoned out unless you’ve got something big on your mind.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “R-right. Yes. Y-you know that sweet shop on the far side of town?” Ethan asked. Getting casual hugs from Sage wasn’t uncommon, but this series of preemptive strikes vaporized any confidence he had built up on the way here.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Oh, Sweet Cute, what about it?” Sage replied, sitting back down.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “They’vegotalimitedtimefallfruitsmenustartingSaturdayWannacheckitoutwithme?” Ethan exhaled. His eyes darted all over the place like an overclocked bouncing DVD logo, his conscious and subconscious fighting whether or not to make eye contact with Sage’s striking sun-kissed brown eyes. ‘Gods, their signature black winged eyeliner with purple accents always goes so hard,’ Ethan thought.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Okay slow down,” Sage said, trying to process what they just heard. “A new limited time menu this Saturday?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     Ethan nodded timidly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Yeah I’m down! Ooh, wanna pretend to be a couple to get that couple’s discount?” Sage responded with a scheming look on their face.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Wh-what??” Ethan tried not to blush but was failing to do so. Of course Sage would know about that, it’s one of the prime date spots specifically because of that.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Yeah, the couple’s discount,” Sage said as they looked up the website on their laptop to show Ethan. “It’s like their staple thing. I’m surprised you didn’t know already.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “N-no, I knew about that, but—”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “—For Elain– er, Ethan?” The barista at the counter interrupted.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “I-I think that might be me, brb,” Ethan said then got up to head towards the barista and take a much-needed breather. It turned out to be his order, so he thanked the barista and headed back, sitting down next to Sage again.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Ooh whatcha get!”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Large matcha latte. W-wanna try?” Ethan held his drink out to Sage, his hand quivering slightly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Mmm, nah I’m good, not feeling matcha right now. Now where were we?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Th-the couple’s discount?” Ethan said then took a sip of his latte.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Ah, yes! It’s simple really,” Sage went on, reaching across Ethan’s shoulders. “Obviously it saves money, and we’d stick out less since most of the people there are gonna be couples anyway. And don’t worry, I’ll be the girl. Unless, of course, you want to.” Sage said, giving Ethan the irl equivalent of the :3 face. “I know you’d look cute.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “I- I- um, no, I,” Ethan.exe has stopped responding, covering his embering cheeks with his hands. He shouldn’t’ve let Sage dress him up as a girl for Halloween last year, too many thoughts sprung from that moment that he did not want to think about, yet here he was, mind racing because of it. Like why is Sage’s offer so tempting? Why was that Halloween the best he’d ever had? Why was that girl in the mirror so—&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Hey, hey, you okay, E?” Sage tugged on his arm, yanking him out of his thoughts. “You’re doing the thing again. Did I go too far with my jokes? It’s okay, we don’t have to do the couples thing if you don’t want to.” Sage pulled away a little, lowering their head.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “N-no you’re right, the discount is too good to pass up,” Ethan got out. He took a deep breath, sipped on his latte again, then said, “You can be the girl, I know you’ll look great,” and smiled.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Yayyyy!” Sage exclaimed, giving Ethan an over-the-shoulder hug. “This’ll be so much fun—”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     An alarm abruptly rang from Ethan’s pant pocket, causing both of them to jump back in their seats a bit. Ethan pulled his phone out, silencing the ‘Head to Class (Sage)’ alarm. “Ack, gotta go,” Ethan said, standing up and grabbing his latte. “See you Saturday?”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Mhm! See you then!” Sage waved goodbye.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     Friday passed by in a blur, with the two’s only interactions being sending each other memes on Discord and confirming when and where to meet up for their outing tomorrow, agreeing to meet at Sage’s place at noon then take the trolley down to Sweet Cute together.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     A chilling breeze was whirling down the street as Ethan approached Sage’s apartment on foot. He was relieved he decided to wear one of his nice warm sweaters as the overhead sun was obscured by a bed of grey cumulus, though it did nothing for his pounding heart as he reached his friend’s door and gave it a few knocks. He heard a faint, “It’s unlocked!” and then proceeded to open the door and walk in, his eyes widening immediately after. While Ethan had seen Sage casually dress femme before, this was on another level. Descending from the carpeted stairs was an absolute beauty. Their black hair that they normally kept in a bun was let down, revealing its true length and waviness. Their signature striking eyes were further enhanced with mascara and the purple accents swapped out with a deep red to match the burgundy A-line dress with black detailing that showed off Sage’s often unseen figure.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Wow,” Ethan gasped in awe, “Sage, you look…” Ethan was at a loss for words, unfamiliar thoughts of envy surfacing in his head.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Aww thanks Ethan,” Sage beamed in response as they sat down on the last step to put their black 3-inch wedge sandals on.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Hm?” Ethan blanked, then came back to his senses. “Oh! Right! A lil something for you.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Omigosh! Bougainvillea! Thank you!!” Sage went in for a hug, receiving the flowers in the process, then dashed to find a vase in the kitchen. Ethan took a few deep breaths, trying not to short circuit, when he felt Sage hold his hand and tiptoe to kiss him on the cheek.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Ready for our ‘pretend’ date?” Sage asked with a glint in their eyes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “As ready as I’ll ever be, but what’s with the air quotes?” Ethan chuckled somewhat nervously.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;     “Oh Ethan,” Sage tiptoed again but this time wrapped their arms around Ethan’s neck, their eyes locked and faces mere centimeters apart, “I already knew.”&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
